-- Mets Sign Pitcher Jonathon Niese to Five-Year Contract Extension
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-04-07T17:23:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-07/mets-sign-pitcher-jonathon-niese-to-five-year-contract-extension.html
The  New York Mets  signed left-handed
pitcher Jonathon Niese to a five-year contract extension, the
Major League Baseball team said in a statement.  Niese, 25, was 11-11 with a 4.40 earned run average in 27
games, with 26 starts, last season. He’s 22-23 with a 4.39 ERA
in 65 games since making his major-league debut in 2008.  The Mets didn’t disclose financial terms of the contract,
which includes two additional club option years that would keep
Niese with the team through 2018.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  